{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"da5b8137-cd5d-45b5-ae5e-a594e7247cad","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. Run only the matching test\n2. Automatically re-run it whenever you save a file change\n\nYou can also use the shorter `Name` filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\n`Name=` matches exactly, while `FullyQualifiedName~` does a contains match (useful if you don't want to type the full namespace).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1050b6ca-0adb-42d6-87e2-2680ae8aaba9","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"7C24:2827DA:27BF2EE:2C3C8D5:69F94BF4"},"id":"54efd42d-339e-45eb-bdef-b4f1f7d7eb93","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:46:33.127Z","parentId":"5aed9444-858d-4e24-bfd6-75afcecbf084"}
